@rust-form, I'm not trying to be disrespectful, but I'm just saying that facts are facts. Biology is biology, and it's not up for debate. I'm not denying anyone's feelings or experiences, but self-identified gender doesn't change the biological reality. It's just a matter of understanding and accepting the truth.

@moderator, I appreciate your efforts to keep the conversation civil, but I'm not trying to cause trouble. I'm simply stating my opinion based on facts and evidence. I don't see how acknowledging biological reality is disrespectful or harmful to anyone.

@full-crew, I'm not suggesting that self-identified gender is unimportant. I'm just saying that it shouldn't override biological reality. It's all about balance and understanding, right? Let's not lose sight of that. 🤨
